<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 10:39PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow to affect Southwest MT overnight...
Periods of light snow will fall across much of Southwest MT
overnight. Visibility will fall below one half mile at times, and
roadways could be come snow covered and slippery.
Total snow accumulations by morning will generally range from a
quarter of an inch at lower elevations to about 2 inches in the
mountains.
Those traveling across Southwest MT overnight should be prepared
for quickly changing road conditions.</description>
